==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Chimera
<hw>Chime"ra</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Chimeras</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[L. <ets>chimaera</ets> a
chimera (in sense 1), Gr. <?/ a she-goat, a chimera, fr. <?/ he-goat;
cf. Icel. <ets>qymbr</ets> a yearling ewe.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Myth.)</fld> <def>A monster represented as vomiting flames, and as
having the head of a lion, the body of a goat, and the tail of a
dragon.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧Dire <xex>chimeras</xex> and enchanted
isles.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A vain, foolish, or incongruous fancy, or creature
of the imagination; <as>as, the <ex>chimera</ex> of an
author</as>.</def> <rj><au>Burke.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Chimere</ent>⟦br⟧
